(3) Upon application being made to him for the renewal of a firearm licence an officer in charge of police shall satisfy himself that— (a) the person presenting the licence for renewal is the authorised holder thereof; (b) the firearms produced to him are those to which the licence relates; (c) the holder of the licence is still a fit and proper person to be entrusted with the firearms in question and that the purposes for which such firearms are required are still lawful; (d) the firearms are not in a dangerous condition; and if he is so satisfied he shall endorse on the firearm licence that the firearms to which it relates have been produced to him and that such licence may be renewed.
